CommonFields.Title: Rubber-clay nanocomposite by solution blending
Author: Pramanik, Monoj
Srivastava, Suneel Kumar
Samantaray, Biswas Kumar
Bhowmick, Anil Kumar
CommonFields.Location: Department of Chemistry, Indian Institute of Technology, Kharagpur‐721302, India

Mixing.Description: EVA-45 was added to the dry DMAc at 85°C and stirred to attain a jellylike solution

Additive.Description: Dicumyl peroxide was added and the mixture was dried under reduced pressure

MoldingInfo.Description: Mixture was compression-molded by a hydraulically operated press at 150°C for 45 min to obtain nanocomposites

Transmission_Electron_Microscopy.Description: Used to observe the dispersion of organophilic clay in the EVA-45 matrix and nanofeatures

Scanning_Electron_Microscopy.Description: Used to observe the dispersion of organophilic clay in the EVA-45 matrix and nanofeatures

Dynamic_Mechanical_Analysis.Description: Used to measure the dynamic mechanical properties

Fourier_Transform_Infrared_Spectroscopy.Description: The IR spectra of the nanocomposites were recorded on a Perkin–Elmer 883 IR spectrometer over a frequency range of 200–4000 cm-1
